    ViewData["Title"] = "About Waikirikiri";
}
@*<img src="~/img/Marae-Preview-ConvertImage (3).png" class="about-us-image" alt="Waikirikiri" />*@
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-12 pepeha">
        <h2>Ko Parekohe te maunga</h2>
        <h2>Ko Ōhinemataroa te awa</h2>
        <h2>Ko Waikirikiri te marae</h2>
        <h2>Ko Toi Kairākau te wharepuni</h2>
        <h2>Ko Kura-i-mōnoa te wharekai</h2>
        <h2>Ko Hāmua – Ngāti Mura ngā hapū</h2>
        <h2>Ko Ngai Tūhoe te iwi</h2>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="about-content">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-12 purpose">
            <h2>Our Purpose</h2>
            <p>The purpose of Waikirikiri marae’s website is to host our Hāmua hapū registration database.</p>
            <p>The focus of the database is threefold;</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Gain a clear understanding of our hapū’s profile (overall population; place of residence; age bands of hapū members; proficiency in te reo etc)</li>
                <li>Using the information gained in the database, Waikirikiri Marae Committee can make strategic decisions informed by our hapū profile  </li>
                <li>Increase communication between Waikirikiri's Marae Committee and descendants of Hāmua</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>
                Why Register?
            </h3>

            <ul>
                <li>Connect with Waikirikiri marae and Hāmua nui tonu</li>
                <li>Update the whakapapa of Hāmua</li>
                <li>Stay up to date with marae and hapū developments and initiatives</li>
                <li>Can assist with the future of Waikirikiri and Hāmua whether near or far</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="committee-members">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-12">
                <h2>Committee Members</h2>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-4">
                <div class="committee-member-img-container img-thumbnail">
                    <img class="committee-member" src="~/img/WMCChair-RamekaTuhaka.jpg" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-8 committe-member-blurb">
                <h3>Rāmeka (Ray) Tuhaka - Chairman</h3>
                <p>
                    Ko Rāmeka Tuhaka tōku ingoa. Ko Ani rāua ko Armis ōku pākeke. No Rangitukia ki Tikitiki taku Pāpā. Nō Rūātoki taku Māmā.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ko au te Tiamana o te Komiti o te Marae o Waikirikiri. Kei Tūhoe Hauora ahau e mahi ana. Ko taku mahi, he kimi awhina mo ngā tangata haua/whai kaha(Disability Support Services) I roto i o rātau kainga. Ko aku kai reka rawa ki ahau ko ngā kai o te marae.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ko Rūātoki Sports and Cultural Club te tino karapu o te ao! Ko taku harikoa ka kite ana I ngā tāngata Pakeke/Rangatahi/Tamariki o te hapū o Hāmua/Ngāti Mura kua eke ki roto I nga tohu teitei o te Hakinakina, I roto I ngā kura puta noa ki ngā Whare Wananga. Otira puta noa ki te whārua o Rūātoki. Mauri Ora.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr />
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-4">
                <div class="committee-member-img-container img-thumbnail">
                    <img class="committee-member" src="~/img/AtaRuawai-Treasurer.2jpg.png" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-8 committe-member-blurb">
                <h3>Ata Ruawai - Treasurer</h3>
                <p>
                    Tena koutou katoa. Ki te taha ō tōku Māmā ko Waikirikiri te marae, ko Hāmua me Ngāti Mura ngā hapū. Ki te taha ō tōku Pāpā ko Ngāhina te marae, ko Ngāti Tāwhaki te hapū. Nō Ruātoki ahau. Ko Tauwhiri me Koro Rua ōku pākeke.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ko Vila Ruawai tōku hoa rangatira. E toru ō māua tamariki. Ko au te kai pupuri pūtea mo te komiti marae ō Waikirikiri.
                    Ko māua ko Vila ngā kaiwhakaere o Te Puna Reo ō Hinemataroa Montessori, ki te kura ō Taneatua.
                </p>
                <p>
                    E tino ngākau nui ana ahau ki te poipoi i ngā tamariki nohinohi kia tū pakari, tū maia i tō rātou ao. Ko ahau hoki tētahi ō ngā kaihaka mō Te Kapa Haka ō Ruātoki/Te Karu. E arohanui ana ahau ki taku kapa, otira ki ngā kapa ō Tūhoe.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Kia Ora!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr />
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-sm-4">
                <div class="committee-member-img-container img-thumbnail">
                    <img class="committee-member" src="~/img/MereDillon-Secretary.jpg" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm-8 committe-member-blurb">
                <h3>Mere Dillon - Secretary</h3>
                <p>
                    Ko Mereana tōku ingoa, ko au te mataamua o
                    Hora rāua ko Wayne Dillon.
                    No Ruatoki tōku māmā, ā, no Pare Hauraki tōku pāpā.
                    Kei Ruatoki au e noho ana.
                    Ko au te hekeretari o te komiti o te marae.
                    Ko te tikanga o taua mahi rā, he tonotono noaiho
                    mo ngā kaumatua o to tātou marae.
                </p>
                <p>
                    E tautoko ana i ngā kōrero ā Rameka Tuhaka mo te
                    Kapa whutupōro o Ruatoki, ēngari ko te “B TEAM” pea te tiima pai rawa!!!
                </p>
                <p>
                    Ko te tumanako kei te noho pai mai koutou i roto i o koutou kainga maha huri noa i te motu.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <hr />
    </div>
</div>
